Long ago, on the distant and odoriferous Planet Stink, there ruled a most peculiar and demanding monarch: Emperor Gupta the Fragrant, whose passion for efficiency was rivaled only by his insatiable thirst for cosmic dominance.
One fateful morning, the Emperor summoned the brightest engineers of his empire and issued a decree that would shake the very foundations of intergalactic linguistics: “Construct for me,” he declared, his voice echoing through the sulfurous skies, “a Communication Network of Words, so that every word in my royal dictionary may reach every other word - not through speech, not through writing, but through transformation itself!”
The task, however, was not one of mere cables or signals. No, the Emperor demanded a network forged in edits. Two words are said to be connected if one can be transformed into the other by a sequence of edit operations, where each operation may be:
●	Insertion - inserting a single character at any position in the word.
●	Deletion - removing a single character from the word.
●	Replacement - changing a single character in the word to another.
Each operation is costly - every insertion, deletion, or replacement extracts the soul of his citizens. The Emperor, merciful as he was tyrannical, sought to minimize the total number of souls lost.
Given a collection of words from the royal lexicon, Emperor Gupta demands to know: What is the minimum total cost, in citizen souls, required to ensure that every word in the network is connected to every other, either directly or through a series of edit transformations?
Input
The problem starts with the integer, t, the number of test cases in the problem (1 <= t <= 1000).
For each test case, you are given an integer, n, the number of words that will be used within the network
(1 <= n <= 100), along with an integer m, the number of souls each edit will cost (1 <= m <= 10).

The next n lines, there will be a word (alphanumeric), with no whitespaces included. Upper and lower cases matter.
Output
For each test case, output the minimum number of souls to create the communication network.
Example Input File
2
3 2
testCase
testBase
bestBase
4 3
planet
blanket
gupta
wupta
Example Output
4
27
